<p><font size="3" face="Arial">This example will show a case where a user creates a Business Unit but no data roles are created so they have to create and assign them manually. The various stages will be broken down into the following headings:<br /></font><strong><font size="3" face="Arial"></font></strong></p>
<ul>
<li><strong><font size="2" face="Arial">Create Basic Business Unit (BU)</font></strong></li>
<li><strong><font size="2" face="Arial">Check if BU Data Roles have been created </font></strong></li>
<li><strong><font size="2" face="Arial">Create Data Roles</font></strong></li>
<li><strong><font size="2" face="Arial">Synchronize Oracle Identity Manager (OIM) with Authorization Policy Manager (APM)</font></strong></li>
<li><strong><font size="2" face="Arial">Assign Data Roles to Login User</font></strong></li>
<li><strong><font size="2" face="Arial">Check Access to BU</font></strong></li>
</ul>
<p><a name="aref_section22"><font size="3" face="Arial"></font></a><br />
<h5><font size="3" face="Arial"></font>&#160;</h5>
<h5><font size="3" face="Arial"></font><font style="font-weight: bold">Create Basic Business Unit (BU)</font></h5>
</p>
<p><a href="http://www.yunning.net/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/downloadattachmentprocessor1.png"><font size="3" face="Arial"><img title="downloadattachmentprocessor(1)" style="border-top: 0px; border-right: 0px; background-image: none; border-bottom: 0px; padding-top: 0px; padding-left: 0px; border-left: 0px; display: inline; padding-right: 0px" border="0" alt="downloadattachmentprocessor(1)" src="http://www.yunning.net/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/downloadattachmentprocessor1_thumb.png" width="769" height="230"/></font></a><br /><font size="3" face="Arial">After picking the &#8216;Define Business Units&#8217; task list create Business Unit. Then save and close. Note This user has created a new default set called &#8216;NC_BU110S&#8217;. It will hold any new set_id data used by the BU &#8216;NC BU110&#8217;.<br /></font><a href="http://www.yunning.net/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/downloadattachmentprocessor2.png"><font size="3" face="Arial"><img title="downloadattachmentprocessor(2)" style="border-top: 0px; border-right: 0px; background-image: none; border-bottom: 0px; padding-top: 0px; padding-left: 0px; border-left: 0px; display: inline; padding-right: 0px" border="0" alt="downloadattachmentprocessor(2)" src="http://www.yunning.net/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/downloadattachmentprocessor2_thumb.png" width="699" height="427"/></font></a><br /><font size="3" face="Arial">Once the initial BU has been created Business Functions need to be assigned. Assigning functions to a BU should automatically create the related data role. In the above example the user is assigning Receivable functionality to a BU named &#8216;NC BU110&#8217;.</font> </p>
<p><a name="aref_section23"><font size="3" face="Arial"></font></a><br />
<h5><font size="3" face="Arial"></font>&#160;</h5>
<h5><font size="3" face="Arial"></font><font style="font-weight: bold">Check if BU Data Roles have been created</font></h5>
</p>
<p><a href="http://www.yunning.net/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/downloadattachmentprocessor3.png"><font size="3" face="Arial"><img title="downloadattachmentprocessor(3)" style="border-top: 0px; border-right: 0px; background-image: none; border-bottom: 0px; padding-top: 0px; padding-left: 0px; border-left: 0px; display: inline; padding-right: 0px" border="0" alt="downloadattachmentprocessor(3)" src="http://www.yunning.net/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/downloadattachmentprocessor3_thumb.png" width="728" height="372"/></font></a><br /><font size="3" face="Arial">Check if the BU is available to pick when configuring the relevant module. In this worked example the user has chosen the receivable functionality. If they cannot pick &#8216;NC BU110&#8217;&#160; when configuring the receivables system options then it&#8217;s likely the relevant data role has either not been created or not assigned.<br />To check if the data role exists log into the Authorization Policy Manager (APM) module. Under the &#8216;Authorization Management&#8217; tab click on the Search External Roles.<br /></font><a href="http://www.yunning.net/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/downloadattachmentprocessor4.png"><font size="3" face="Arial"><img title="downloadattachmentprocessor(4)" style="border-top: 0px; border-right: 0px; background-image: none; border-bottom: 0px; padding-top: 0px; padding-left: 0px; border-left: 0px; display: inline; padding-right: 0px" border="0" alt="downloadattachmentprocessor(4)" src="http://www.yunning.net/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/downloadattachmentprocessor4_thumb.png" width="714" height="466"/></font></a><br /><font size="3" face="Arial">For the basic BU setup there should be two data roles created under the &#8216;Financial Application Administrator&#8217; role. One will be for the basic BU access and the other for the BU set_id access. In the above case neither role has been created &#8216;NC BU100&#8217; BU.<br />For each functionality there will be additional roles required. An example will be shown in the latter steps of this document.</font> </p>
<p><a name="aref_section24"><font size="3" face="Arial"></font></a><br />
<h5><font size="3" face="Arial"></font>&#160;</h5>
<h5><font size="3" face="Arial"></font><font style="font-weight: bold">Create Data Roles</font></h5>
</p>
<p><a href="http://www.yunning.net/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/downloadattachmentprocessor5.png"><font size="3" face="Arial"><img title="downloadattachmentprocessor(5)" style="border-top: 0px; border-right: 0px; background-image: none; border-bottom: 0px; padding-top: 0px; padding-left: 0px; border-left: 0px; display: inline; padding-right: 0px" border="0" alt="downloadattachmentprocessor(5)" src="http://www.yunning.net/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/downloadattachmentprocessor5_thumb.png" width="706" height="317"/></font></a><br /><font size="3" face="Arial">To create a data role the user first needs to search and pick the relevant data role template. <br /></font><a href="http://www.yunning.net/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/downloadattachmentprocessor6.png"><font size="3" face="Arial"><img title="downloadattachmentprocessor(6)" style="border-top: 0px; border-right: 0px; background-image: none; border-bottom: 0px; padding-top: 0px; padding-left: 0px; border-left: 0px; display: inline; padding-right: 0px" border="0" alt="downloadattachmentprocessor(6)" src="http://www.yunning.net/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/downloadattachmentprocessor6_thumb.png" width="724" height="316"/></font></a><br /><font size="3" face="Arial">There are two templates used for the minimum BU usage these are:<br />FinancialsFunBusinessUnit = used for basic BU setup<br />FinancialsFunSetIdFinancialsFunSetId = BU SetId usage<br />In this example as we have assign receivable functionality there should be 2 additional templates which are:<br />BillingRevMgtandCustPayment = Basic AR setup<br />FinancialsArSetIdFinancialsArSetId = AR SetId<br />Once the correct template is shown the user needs to highlight the required template then click on open.<br /></font><a href="http://www.yunning.net/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/downloadattachmentprocessor7.png"><font size="3" face="Arial"><img title="downloadattachmentprocessor(7)" style="border-top: 0px; border-right: 0px; background-image: none; border-bottom: 0px; padding-top: 0px; padding-left: 0px; border-left: 0px; display: inline; padding-right: 0px" border="0" alt="downloadattachmentprocessor(7)" src="http://www.yunning.net/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/downloadattachmentprocessor7_thumb.png" width="590" height="297"/></font></a><br /><font size="3" face="Arial">Once the template has been opened the user can view existing data roles. If they want to create new roles then they need to click on &#8216;Generate Roles&#8217; as shown above.<br /></font><a href="http://www.yunning.net/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/downloadattachmentprocessor8.png"><font size="3" face="Arial"><img title="downloadattachmentprocessor(8)" style="border-top: 0px; border-right: 0px; background-image: none; border-bottom: 0px; padding-top: 0px; padding-left: 0px; border-left: 0px; display: inline; padding-right: 0px" border="0" alt="downloadattachmentprocessor(8)" src="http://www.yunning.net/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/downloadattachmentprocessor8_thumb.png" width="590" height="362"/></font></a><br /><font size="3" face="Arial">Once the &#8216;Generate Roles&#8217; has completed the user can click on &#8216;refresh role&#8217; under &#8216;valid roles&#8217;, In the above example it shows a data role for basic BU usage has been successfully created &#8211; &#8216;FUN_FINANCIAL_APPLICATION_ADMINISTRATOR_JOB_NC BU110&#8217;.<br />When the FinancialsFunSetIdFinancialsFunSetId template is used it will create set_id data role called &#8216;FUN_FINANCIAL_APPLICATION_ADMINISTRATOR_JOB_NC BU110S&#8217;.<br /></font><a href="http://www.yunning.net/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/downloadattachmentprocessor9.png"><font size="3" face="Arial"><img title="downloadattachmentprocessor(9)" style="border-top: 0px; border-right: 0px; background-image: none; border-bottom: 0px; padding-top: 0px; padding-left: 0px; border-left: 0px; display: inline; padding-right: 0px" border="0" alt="downloadattachmentprocessor(9)" src="http://www.yunning.net/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/downloadattachmentprocessor9_thumb.png" width="528" height="412"/></font></a><br /><font size="3" face="Arial">As this example is using receivables functionality when the template FinancialsArSetIdFinancialsArSetId is used to generate data roles then all AR roles will have a set_id role created for them. As as shown above. </font> </p>
<p><a name="aref_section25"><font size="3" face="Arial"></font></a><br />
<h5><font size="3" face="Arial"></font>&#160;</h5>
<h5><font size="3" face="Arial"></font><font style="font-weight: bold">Synchronize Oracle Identity Manager (OIM) with Authorization Policy Manager (APM)</font></h5>
</p>
<p><a href="http://www.yunning.net/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/downloadattachmentprocessor10.png"><font size="3" face="Arial"><img title="downloadattachmentprocessor(10)" style="border-top: 0px; border-right: 0px; background-image: none; border-bottom: 0px; padding-top: 0px; padding-left: 0px; border-left: 0px; display: inline; padding-right: 0px" border="0" alt="downloadattachmentprocessor(10)" src="http://www.yunning.net/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/downloadattachmentprocessor10_thumb.png" width="611" height="229"/></font></a><br /><font size="3" face="Arial">Once the data roles have been successfully created in APM they then need to be copied over to OIM. To do this you can either run &#8216;LDAP Role Create and Update Full Reconciliation&#8217; or &#8216;LDAP Role Create and Update Reconciliation&#8217; program. To run either program you will need to go into OIM and click on the &#8216;Advance&#8217; icon as shown above.<br /></font><a href="http://www.yunning.net/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/downloadattachmentprocessor11.png"><font size="3" face="Arial"><img title="downloadattachmentprocessor(11)" style="border-top: 0px; border-right: 0px; background-image: none; border-bottom: 0px; padding-top: 0px; padding-left: 0px; border-left: 0px; display: inline; padding-right: 0px" border="0" alt="downloadattachmentprocessor(11)" src="http://www.yunning.net/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/downloadattachmentprocessor11_thumb.png" width="627" height="382"/></font></a><br /><font size="3" face="Arial">Once in OIM&#8217;s Advance Administration section pick the &#8216;System Management&#8217; tab then select either of the LDAP reconciliation scheduled jobs. Now double click on the chosen job to open up it&#8217;s parameters.<br /></font><a href="http://www.yunning.net/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/downloadattachmentprocessor111.png"><font size="3" face="Arial"><img title="downloadattachmentprocessor(11)[1]" style="border-top: 0px; border-right: 0px; background-image: none; border-bottom: 0px; padding-top: 0px; padding-left: 0px; border-left: 0px; display: inline; padding-right: 0px" border="0" alt="downloadattachmentprocessor(11)[1]" src="http://www.yunning.net/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/downloadattachmentprocessor111_thumb.png" width="631" height="385"/></font></a><br /><font size="3" face="Arial">After opening the parameters section of the job click on &#8216;Run Now&#8217;. This will then copy all the successfully created data roles from APM into OIM.&#160; The next step will to assign these data roles to a login user.</font> </p>
<p><a name="aref_section26"><font size="3" face="Arial"></font></a><br />
<h5><font size="3" face="Arial"></font>&#160;</h5>
<h5><font size="3" face="Arial"></font><font style="font-weight: bold">Assign Data Roles to Login User </font></h5>
</p>
<p><a href="http://www.yunning.net/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/downloadattachmentprocessor12.png"><font size="3" face="Arial"><img title="downloadattachmentprocessor(12)" style="border-top: 0px; border-right: 0px; background-image: none; border-bottom: 0px; padding-top: 0px; padding-left: 0px; border-left: 0px; display: inline; padding-right: 0px" border="0" alt="downloadattachmentprocessor(12)" src="http://www.yunning.net/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/downloadattachmentprocessor12_thumb.png" width="672" height="229"/></font></a><br /><font size="3" face="Arial">When in OIM under the &#8216;Administration&#8217; tab click on the users &#8216;Advance Search -Users&#8217; section. <br /></font><a href="http://www.yunning.net/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/downloadattachmentprocessor13.png"><font size="3" face="Arial"><img title="downloadattachmentprocessor(13)" style="border-top: 0px; border-right: 0px; background-image: none; border-bottom: 0px; padding-top: 0px; padding-left: 0px; border-left: 0px; display: inline; padding-right: 0px" border="0" alt="downloadattachmentprocessor(13)" src="http://www.yunning.net/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/downloadattachmentprocessor13_thumb.png" width="692" height="362"/></font></a><br /><font size="3" face="Arial">In this example the user would like the login user &#8216;fin_superuser&#8217; to be able to use the BU &#8216;NC_BU110&#8217;. Therefore they will need to assign these roles to this login user. Once the user has found &#8216;fin_superuser&#8217; they will need to pick this user in the research results field then click on open.<br /></font><a href="http://www.yunning.net/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/downloadattachmentprocessor14.png"><font size="3" face="Arial"><img title="downloadattachmentprocessor(14)" style="border-top: 0px; border-right: 0px; background-image: none; border-bottom: 0px; padding-top: 0px; padding-left: 0px; border-left: 0px; display: inline; padding-right: 0px" border="0" alt="downloadattachmentprocessor(14)" src="http://www.yunning.net/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/downloadattachmentprocessor14_thumb.png" width="730" height="258"/></font></a><br /><font size="3" face="Arial">Once the user is in the required login user. Here it is showing the &#8216;FIN_SUPERUSER&#8217; tab. Then click on the assign icon to pick which roles you want assigned.<br /></font><a href="http://www.yunning.net/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/downloadattachmentprocessor15.png"><font size="3" face="Arial"><img title="downloadattachmentprocessor(15)" style="border-top: 0px; border-right: 0px; background-image: none; border-bottom: 0px; padding-top: 0px; padding-left: 0px; border-left: 0px; display: inline; padding-right: 0px" border="0" alt="downloadattachmentprocessor(15)" src="http://www.yunning.net/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/downloadattachmentprocessor15_thumb.png" width="677" height="542"/></font></a><br /><font size="3" face="Arial">The above example shows the user assigning basic BU access data role for BU &#8216;NC BU110&#8217; to the login user &#8216;FIN_SUPERUSER&#8217;.<br /></font><a href="http://www.yunning.net/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/downloadattachmentprocessor16.png"><font size="3" face="Arial"><img title="downloadattachmentprocessor(16)" style="border-top: 0px; border-right: 0px; background-image: none; border-bottom: 0px; padding-top: 0px; padding-left: 0px; border-left: 0px; display: inline; padding-right: 0px" border="0" alt="downloadattachmentprocessor(16)" src="http://www.yunning.net/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/downloadattachmentprocessor16_thumb.png" width="652" height="512"/></font></a><br /><font size="3" face="Arial">As the user has assigned Receivable functionality to this BU they also need to assign the AR roles ,such as the &#8216;AR_BILLING_MANAGER&#8217;, to this login user.</font> </p>
<p><a name="aref_section27"><font size="3" face="Arial"></font></a><br />
<h5><font size="3" face="Arial"></font>&#160;</h5>
<h5><font size="3" face="Arial"></font><font style="font-weight: bold">Check Access to BU</font></h5>
</p>
<p><a href="http://www.yunning.net/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/downloadattachmentprocessor17.png"><font size="3" face="Arial"><img title="downloadattachmentprocessor(17)" style="border-top: 0px; border-right: 0px; background-image: none; border-bottom: 0px; padding-top: 0px; padding-left: 0px; border-left: 0px; display: inline; padding-right: 0px" border="0" alt="downloadattachmentprocessor(17)" src="http://www.yunning.net/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/downloadattachmentprocessor17_thumb.png" width="662" height="468"/></font></a><br /><font size="3" face="Arial">To show the user now has access to the newly created&#160; &#8216;NC BU110&#8217; BU they can go to any AR configuration step to see if this BU is available in the LOV. Here the user has chosen the &#8216;Receivable Activities&#8217; task.<br /></font><a href="http://www.yunning.net/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/downloadattachmentprocessor18.png"><font size="3" face="Arial"><img title="downloadattachmentprocessor(18)" style="border-top: 0px; border-right: 0px; background-image: none; border-bottom: 0px; padding-top: 0px; padding-left: 0px; border-left: 0px; display: inline; padding-right: 0px" border="0" alt="downloadattachmentprocessor(18)" src="http://www.yunning.net/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/downloadattachmentprocessor18_thumb.png" width="720" height="285"/></font></a><br /><font size="3" face="Arial">The data roles have correctly been created and assign as they are now able to pick BU &#8216;NC BU110&#8217;.</font></p>
